## Evidence Summary

### Root Cause

The queue-row elapsed is anchored to **execute-start** (stage 5), not the **overall pipeline start** (planning stages 1–4). The single dictionary `_runStartedAt` in `MainWindowViewModel.cs` has exactly one writer — `BeginRunningTask` (`LiveState.cs` line 112) — which is called at `OnExecuteStarted` in a drain (Phase 2, serial execute). Phase 1 (parallel planning) fires `OnPlanningStarted` but never records a start time.

### Supporting Excerpts

**1. `_runStartedAt` is declared in `MainWindowViewModel.cs:38` — the sole anchor for queue-row elapsed**
```
private readonly Dictionary<string, DateTimeOffset> _runStartedAt = new(StringComparer.Ordinal);
```

**2. Single writer: `BeginRunningTask` at `LiveState.cs:106-119` — unconditional indexer assignment**
```csharp
private void BeginRunningTask(TaskRowViewModel task)
{
    _runningTaskIds.Add(task.Id);
    _runningTaskId = task.Id;
    _runningStageNumbers[task.Id] = null;
    _runningStageNames[task.Id] = null;
    _runStartedAt[task.Id] = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow;   // <-- line 112
    ...
}
```

**3. `BeginRunningTask` called from `OnExecuteStarted` (drain) at `LiveState.cs:31-41` — execute-phase only**
```csharp
OnExecuteStarted = taskId =>
{
    StatusText = $"Running {taskId}";
    var task = Tasks.FirstOrDefault(t => t.Id == taskId);
    if (task is not null)
        BeginRunningTask(task);   // <-- line 40: sets _runStartedAt at execute-start (stage 5)
},
```

**4. `OnPlanningStarted` at `LiveState.cs:15-18` — does NOT record `_runStartedAt`**
```csharp
OnPlanningStarted = taskId =>
{
    StatusText = $"Planning {taskId}…";
    Tasks.FirstOrDefault(t => t.Id == taskId)?.MarkPlanning();
    // MISSING: _runStartedAt[taskId] = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow;
},
```

**5. Queue-row elapsed computed from `_runStartedAt` only — `UpdateRunningElapsedLabels` at `LiveState.cs:188-201`**
```csharp
public void UpdateRunningElapsedLabels()
{
    var now = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow;
    foreach (var taskId in _runningTaskIds)
    {
        if (_runStartedAt.TryGetValue(taskId, out var startedAt))
        {
            var task = Tasks.FirstOrDefault(t => t.Id == taskId);
            if (task is not null)
                task.RunningElapsedLabel = ElapsedFormatter.Label(now - startedAt);
        }
    }
    ...
}
```

**6. Stage-card elapsed uses a completely separate anchor — `ApplyStageEventToBoard` at `Helpers.cs:88-93`**
```csharp
if (relayEvent.EventName == "stage_start")
{
    stage.MarkRunning(DateTimeOffset.UtcNow);  // <-- separate _runningSince anchor
}
```

**7. `StageRowViewModel.MarkRunning` at `StageRowViewModel.cs:136-141` — stores its own `_runningSince`**
```csharp
public void MarkRunning(DateTimeOffset startedAt)
{
    _runningSince = startedAt;
    ElapsedLabel = string.Empty;
    Status = "Running";
}
```

**8. Drain Phase 1 fires `OnPlanningStarted`, Phase 2 fires `OnExecuteStarted` — `RelayQueueController.cs:131-134, 207`**
```csharp
// Phase 1 (line 131-134):
if (_lifecycle is not null)
    foreach (var (taskId, _) in needsPlan)
        _lifecycle.OnPlanningStarted?.Invoke(taskId);  // no start time captured

// Phase 2 (line 207):
_lifecycle?.OnExecuteStarted?.Invoke(task.Id);  // _runStartedAt set HERE (stage 5 onward)
```

**9. Single-run path is correct — `RunOneAsync` at `Execution.cs:267` calls `BeginRunningTask` before stages 1–11**
```csharp
BeginRunningTask(task);  // line 267: before driver.RunTaskAsync, covers stage 1 onward
...
var outcome = await driver.RunTaskAsync(RootPath, task.Id);  // line 278
```

**10. Line-count constraints confirmed**
- `MainWindowViewModel.cs`: 300 (at limit — no changes allowed)
- `MainWindowViewModel.LiveState.cs`: 279 (room for ~21 lines)
- `MainWindowViewModel.Execution.cs`: 299 (must not add here)
- `MainWindowViewModel.Helpers.cs`: 299 (must not add here)

### Repro

To reproduce the bug: start a drain where planning stages 1–4 are not already Done. Observe the left queue row during Phase 2 (serial execute). The `MetricsLine` shows e.g. `Stage 05 · Author-tests · 4m 49s` — the elapsed counts from `OnExecuteStarted` (the start of stage 5), NOT from `OnPlanningStarted` (the start of the overall task pipeline). Planning stages 1–4 and inter-stage gaps are excluded. Meanwhile the STAGES card shows `Running 4m 46s` — a ~3s offset because `stage.MarkRunning(DateTimeOffset.UtcNow)` fires a few seconds after `_runStartedAt[taskId]` via the event hop through the RelayDriver.

